How can I generate a 10-digit random number in MATLAB without repeating digits?
Here is my current code:
num = randi([1000000000,9999999999],1);
strnum = num2str(num);
if length(unique(strnum)) == length(strnum)
    disp('Unique digits')
else
    disp('Repeating digits')
end
Is there a more efficient way to generate the random number without repeating digits?
